<p>When people think of business writing, they often think of the persuasive writing category. These documents are generally associated with sales. The persuasive writing may be direct, with focus on a specific item, or indirect, with an emphasis on developing the client relationship.</p><p>The goal is to two-fold: to convey information and to convince the reader that the presented information offers the best value. They write the text to impress the reader and sway their decision.</p>
